Description: Rim and wall sherd of East Greek plate or standed dish; simple upturned rim; interior slipped cream; rim glazed inside and out; key maeander at edge of floor, band with added red band to its inside; frieze of alternating red and glaze tongues and dot rosettes; further bands to the centre. Exterior: two bands near top of wall, three further down..
Curator's comments: Compare 1888,0601.544d and Edinburgh A.1886.518.2H, also perhaps UCL-203.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.742)
